4795 /* Write Latitude: */
4796
4797 if ( result ) {
4798 memset( formattedValue, 0, sizeof formattedValue )__builtin___memset_chk (formattedValue, 0, sizeof formattedValue
, __builtin_object_size (formattedValue, 0));
4799 snprintf( formattedValue,__builtin___snprintf_chk (formattedValue, sizeof formattedValue
/ sizeof *formattedValue, 0, __builtin_object_size (formattedValue
, 2 > 1 ? 1 : 0), format, latitude)
4800 sizeof formattedValue / sizeof *formattedValue,__builtin___snprintf_chk (formattedValue, sizeof formattedValue
/ sizeof *formattedValue, 0, __builtin_object_size (formattedValue
, 2 > 1 ? 1 : 0), format, latitude)
4801 format, latitude )__builtin___snprintf_chk (formattedValue, sizeof formattedValue
/ sizeof *formattedValue, 0, __builtin_object_size (formattedValue
, 2 > 1 ? 1 : 0), format, latitude);
4802 result = fwrite( formattedValue, FIELD_WIDTH, 1, file ) == 1;
4803
4804 /* Write Depth: */
4805
4806 if (result ) {
4807
4808 if ( z ) {
4809 memset( formattedValue, 0, sizeof formattedValue )__builtin___memset_chk (formattedValue, 0, sizeof formattedValue
, __builtin_object_size (formattedValue, 0));
4810 snprintf( formattedValue,__builtin___snprintf_chk (formattedValue, sizeof formattedValue
/ sizeof *formattedValue, 0, __builtin_object_size (formattedValue
, 2 > 1 ? 1 : 0), format, depth)
4811 sizeof formattedValue / sizeof *formattedValue,__builtin___snprintf_chk (formattedValue, sizeof formattedValue
/ sizeof *formattedValue, 0, __builtin_object_size (formattedValue
, 2 > 1 ? 1 : 0), format, depth)
4812 format, depth )__builtin___snprintf_chk (formattedValue, sizeof formattedValue
/ sizeof *formattedValue, 0, __builtin_object_size (formattedValue
, 2 > 1 ? 1 : 0), format, depth);
4813 result = fwrite( formattedValue, FIELD_WIDTH, 1, file ) == 1;
4814 }
4815 }
4816 }
4817 }
4818 }
4819 }
4820
4821 fclose( file ), file = 0;
4822 }
4823
4824 if ( ! result ) {
4825 perror( "\n\nFailed to write DBF file because" );
4826 }
4827
4828 memset( header, 0, headerBytes )__builtin___memset_chk (header, 0, headerBytes, __builtin_object_size
(header, 0));
4829 FREE( header )( ( (header) ? free(header) : (void) 0 ), (header) = 0 );
4830 }
4831
4832 if ( result ) {
4833 result = writeDataToCSVFile( fileName, variable, units,
4834 timesteps, yyyymmddhh, timestepType,
4835 count, type, components, data, lonlats,
4836 z, sids );
4837 }
4838
4839 return result;
4840}
4841
4842
4843
4844/******************************************************************************
4845PURPOSE: writeDataToCSVFile - Write location info and
4846 time-varying data to a csv file.
4847INPUTS: const char* fileName Base name of file to create. "IOOS".
4848 const char* variable Name of data variable. E.g., "salinity".
4849 const char* units Name of data units. E.g., "PSU".
4850 const int timesteps Number of timesteps of data.
4851 const int yyyymmddhh[ timesteps ] Timestamps of data.
4852 const int timestepType HOURLY, DAILY, MONTHLY, YEARLY.
4853 const int count Number of data rows, e.g., grid rows x columns.
4854 const int type Data type: BYTE_TYPE, FLOAT_TYPE, etc.
4855 const int components 1 = scalar, 2 or 3 = vector.
4856 const void* data data[ components * timesteps * count ]
4857 Component data at cells.
4858 const float lonlats[ count * 2 ] Lon-lat of each row data point.
4859 const float z[ count ] Depth(m) of each row data point or 0
4860 const char* const sids[ count ] Station id strings or 0.
4861NOTES: Creates file fileName.csv containing static location info:
4862 ID (int) [Station (string)] Longitude Latitude [Depth(m)]
4863 [] denotes optional (if available).
4864 ID is int in range [0, points - 1] index matching shapes in shp file.
4865 Station is string-id for the station, if station data, else omitted.
4866 Depth(m) is omitted if unavailable.
4867 And time-varying data:
4868 YYYYMMDDHH Quantity Units Value
4869 or YYYYMMDD
4870 or YYYYMM
4871 or YYYY
4872 With rows ordered by: ID then timestamp then variable/component.
4873******************************************************************************/
4874
4875static int writeDataToCSVFile( const char* fileName,
4876 const char* variable, const char* units,
4877 const int timesteps, const int yyyymmddhh[],
4878 const int timestepType,
4879 const int count, const int type,
4880 const int components,
4881 const void* data,
4882 const float lonlats[], const float z[],
4883 const char* const sids[] ) {
4884

5526/******************************************************************************
5527PURPOSE: computeVertexBounds - Compute bounds of vertices.
5528INPUTS: const int count Number of vertices.
5529OUTPUTS: const float xy[ Sequence of (x, y) vertices.
5530 double xyRange[ 2 * 2 ] xMin, yMin, xMax, yMax.
5531******************************************************************************/
5532
5533static void computeVertexBounds( const int count, const float xy[],
5534 double xyRange[] ) {
5535
5536 const float* x = xy;
5537 const float* y = xy + 1;
5538 float xMinimum = *x;
5539 float xMaximum = xMinimum;
5540 float yMinimum = *y;
5541 float yMaximum = yMinimum;
5542 int vertex = 0;
5543
5544 for ( vertex = 0; vertex < count; ++vertex, x += 2, y += 2 ) {
5545
5546 if ( *x < xMinimum ) {
5547 xMinimum = *x;
5548 } else if ( *x > xMaximum ) {
5549 xMaximum = *x;
5550 }
5551
5552 if ( *y < yMinimum ) {
5553 yMinimum = *y;
5554 } else if ( *y > yMaximum ) {
5555 yMaximum = *y;
5556 }
5557 }
5558
5559 xyRange[ 0 ] = xMinimum;
5560 xyRange[ 1 ] = yMinimum;
5561 xyRange[ 2 ] = xMaximum;
5562 xyRange[ 3 ] = yMaximum;
5563}

5567/******************************************************************************
5568PURPOSE: computeGridBounds - Compute bounds of grid coordinates.

5783/******************************************************************************
5784PURPOSE: computePointBounds - Compute bounds of point coordinates.
5785INPUTS: const int points Number of points.
5786 const float lonlats[ points * 2 ] Longitude latitude coordinates.
5787OUTPUTS: double range[ 4 ] xMin, yMin, xMax, yMax.
5788******************************************************************************/
5789
5790static void computePointBounds( const int points,
5791 const float lonlats[],
5792 double range[ 4 ] ) {
5793 double minimumX = lonlats[ 0 ];
5794 double maximumX = minimumX;
5795 double minimumY = lonlats[ 1 ];
5796 double maximumY = minimumY;
5797 int point = 0;
5798
5799 /* Check against rest of points: */
5800
5801 for ( point = 1; point < points; ++point ) {
5802 const int point2 = point + point;
5803 const float longitude = lonlats[ point2 ];
5804 const float latitude = lonlats[ point2 + 1 ];
5805
5806 if ( longitude < minimumX ) {
5807 minimumX = longitude;
5808 } else if ( longitude > maximumX ) {
5809 maximumX = longitude;
5810 }
5811
5812 if ( latitude < minimumY ) {
5813 minimumY = latitude;
5814 } else if ( latitude > maximumY ) {
5815 maximumY = latitude;
5816 }
5817 }
5818
5819 range[ 0 ] = minimumX;
5820 range[ 1 ] = minimumY;
5821 range[ 2 ] = maximumX;
5822 range[ 3 ] = maximumY;
5823}

5827/******************************************************************************
5828PURPOSE: computeRange - Compute minimum and maximum value in array.
5829INPUTS: const double array[ count ] Items to examine.
5830 const int count Number of items to compare.
5831 const int stride Stride of index.
5832OUTPUTS: double range[ 2 ] Minimum and maximum values in array.
5833******************************************************************************/
5834
5835static void computeRange( const double array[], const int count,
5836 const int stride, double range[ 2 ] ) {
5837 double minimum = array[ 0 ];
5838 double maximum = minimum;
5839 int index = 0;
5840
5841 for ( index = stride; index < count; index += stride ) {
5842 const double item = array[ index ];
5843
5844 if ( item < minimum ) {
5845 minimum = item;
5846 } else if ( item > maximum ) {
5847 maximum = item;
5848 }
5849 }
5850
5851 range[ 0 ] = minimum;
5852 range[ 1 ] = maximum;
5853}

5859INPUTS: const char* inputFileName File name of input: hms_smoke20161017.dbf
5860 const char* timestamp Timestamp hhmm or yyyyddd hhmm.
5861OUTPUTS: int* const yyyyddd Date.
5862 int* const hhmm Time.
5863RETURNS: int 1 if successful, else 0 failure message is printed.
5864******************************************************************************/
5865
5866static int convertTimestamp( const char* inputFileName,
5867 const char* timestamp,
5868 int* const yyyyddd, int* const hhmm ) {
5869

*)-1L, "Shapefile.c", 5870, "PRE"": ""hhmm"), 0))),&unused_assert_
!=0);

5874 result = sscanf( timestamp, "%d %d", yyyyddd, hhmm ) == 2;
5875
5876 if ( result ) {
5877 result = isValidDate( *yyyyddd );
5878
5879 if ( result ) {
5880 result = isValidTime( *hhmm * 100 );
5881 }
5882 }
5883 } else { /* HHMM only. Parse YYYYMMDD from file name & convert to YYYYDDD: */
5884 const char* const tag = "hms_smoke";
5885 const char* name = strstr( inputFileName, tag );
5886
5887 if ( name ) {
5888 name += strlen( tag );
5889
5890 if ( isdigit( *name ) ) {
5891 const int yyyymmdd = atoi( name );
5892 result = isValidYearMonthDay( yyyymmdd );
5893
5894 if ( result ) {
5895 *yyyyddd = convertYearMonthDay( yyyymmdd );
5896 *hhmm = atoi( timestamp );
5897 result = isValidTime( *hhmm * 100 );
5898 }
5899 }
5900 }
5901 }

5909/******************************************************************************
5910PURPOSE: writeShort - Write a 2-byte integer to a byte array with the given
5911 endian format.
5912INPUTS: const int index Starting index into bytes[] to write.
5913 const short value Value to write.
5914 const int endian Endian format to write.
5915OUTPUTS: unsigned char bytes[] bytes[ index ... index + 4 ].
5916RETURNS: int index + 4.
5917******************************************************************************/
5918
5919static int writeShort( unsigned char bytes[], const int index,
5920 const short value, const int endian ) {
5921 const int result = index + 4;
5922 const unsigned char byte1 = value & 0x00ff;
5923 const unsigned char byte2 = ( value & 0xff00 ) >> 8;
5924
5925 if ( endian == BIG ) {
5926 bytes[ index ] = byte2;
5927 bytes[ index + 1 ] = byte1;
5928 } else {
5929 bytes[ index ] = byte1;
5930 bytes[ index + 1 ] = byte2;
5931 }
5932
5933 return result;
5934}

5938/******************************************************************************
5939PURPOSE: writeInt - Write a 4-byte integer to a byte array with the given
5940 endian format.
5941INPUTS: const int index Starting index into bytes[] to write.
5942 const int value Value to write.
5943 const int endian Endian format to write.
5944OUTPUTS: unsigned char bytes[] bytes[ index ... index + 4 ].
5945RETURNS: int index + 4.
5946******************************************************************************/
5947
5948static int writeInt( unsigned char bytes[], const int index,
5949 const int value, const int endian ) {
5950 const int result = index + 4;
5951 const unsigned char byte1 = value & 0x000000ff;
5952 const unsigned char byte2 = ( value & 0x0000ff00 ) >> 8;
5953 const unsigned char byte3 = ( value & 0x00ff0000 ) >> 16;
5954 const unsigned char byte4 = ( value & 0xff000000 ) >> 24;
5955
5956 if ( endian == BIG ) {
5957 bytes[ index ] = byte4;
5958 bytes[ index + 1 ] = byte3;
5959 bytes[ index + 2 ] = byte2;
5960 bytes[ index + 3 ] = byte1;
5961 } else {
5962 bytes[ index ] = byte1;
5963 bytes[ index + 1 ] = byte2;
5964 bytes[ index + 2 ] = byte3;
5965 bytes[ index + 3 ] = byte4;
5966 }
5967
5968 return result;
5969}

5973/******************************************************************************
5974PURPOSE: writeDouble - Write a 8-byte real to a byte array with the given
5975 endian format.
5976INPUTS: const int index Starting index into bytes[] to write.
5977 const double value Value to write.
5978 const int endian Endian format to write.
5979OUTPUTS: unsigned char bytes[] bytes[ index ... index + 8 ].
5980RETURNS: int index + 8.
5981******************************************************************************/
5982
5983static int writeDouble( unsigned char bytes[], const int index,
5984 const double value, const int endian ) {
5985 const int result = index + 8;
5986 const void* const pvvalue = &value;
5987 const long long* const pivalue = pvvalue;
5988 const long long ivalue = *pivalue;
5989 const unsigned char byte1 = ivalue & 0x00000000000000ffLL;
5990 const unsigned char byte2 = ( ivalue & 0x000000000000ff00LL ) >> 8;
5991 const unsigned char byte3 = ( ivalue & 0x0000000000ff0000LL ) >> 16;
5992 const unsigned char byte4 = ( ivalue & 0x00000000ff000000LL ) >> 24;
5993 const unsigned char byte5 = ( ivalue & 0x000000ff00000000LL ) >> 32;
5994 const unsigned char byte6 = ( ivalue & 0x0000ff0000000000LL ) >> 40;
5995 const unsigned char byte7 = ( ivalue & 0x00ff000000000000LL ) >> 48;
5996 const unsigned char byte8 = ( ivalue & 0xff00000000000000LL ) >> 56;
5997
5998 if ( endian == BIG ) {
5999 bytes[ index ] = byte8;
6000 bytes[ index + 1 ] = byte7;
6001 bytes[ index + 2 ] = byte6;
6002 bytes[ index + 3 ] = byte5;
6003 bytes[ index + 4 ] = byte4;
6004 bytes[ index + 5 ] = byte3;
6005 bytes[ index + 6 ] = byte2;
6006 bytes[ index + 7 ] = byte1;
6007 } else {
6008 bytes[ index ] = byte1;
6009 bytes[ index + 1 ] = byte2;
6010 bytes[ index + 2 ] = byte3;
6011 bytes[ index + 3 ] = byte4;
6012 bytes[ index + 4 ] = byte5;
6013 bytes[ index + 5 ] = byte6;
6014 bytes[ index + 6 ] = byte7;
6015 bytes[ index + 7 ] = byte8;
6016 }
6017
6018 return result;
6019}
